Finding a buyer to buy it in whole is difficult, but piecing it out at a more attainable price is easier. It also allows future stake in the game if you keep pieces for yourself.
The difficulty of owning a grail is the illiquidity that comes with selling it at the right price, but fractionalizing it could be the alternative solution.
I expect the price of rares to increase since fractionalization will allow more people to participate in the ownership of a grail with less risk.
